{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17642899","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17642899"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T19:45:54+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T19:45:54+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17969"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"17969","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/17969"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.7,0.03,0.23,0,0.03]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10683"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"78864"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"10683","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/10683"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17969"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"64213"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4930"},{"type":"tags","id":"4941"},{"type":"tags","id":"7184"},{"type":"tags","id":"7195"},{"type":"tags","id":"7276"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"24879"},{"type":"contributions","id":"24883"},{"type":"contributions","id":"27062"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"78864","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/78864"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EThe trigeminal nerve has motor and sensory functions.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the divisions of this nerve has an efferent branch to the muscles of mastication?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Mandibular (V3)","Maxillary (V2)","Maxillary (V2) and Mandibular (V3)","Ophthalmic (V1)","Ophthalmic (V1) and Maxillary (V2)"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe trigeminal nerve (CN V) is the fifth cranial nerve and has three divisions: the \u003Cstrong\u003Eophthalmic (V1)\u003C/strong\u003E, \u003Cstrong\u003Emaxillary (V2)\u003C/strong\u003E, and \u003Cstrong\u003Emandibular (V3)\u003C/strong\u003E divisions. The ophthalmic and maxillary divisions are purely sensory, providing sensation to the forehead, scalp, and midface, respectively.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Emandibular division (V3)\u003C/strong\u003E is unique in that it carries both sensory and motor fibres. It provides sensory innervation to the lower face, jaw, and anterior two-thirds of the tongue. Importantly, it also contains motor fibres that innervate the muscles of mastication, including the masseter, temporalis, and pterygoid muscles.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003ETherefore, the mandibular division (V3) is the only division of the trigeminal nerve with an efferent branch to the muscles of mastication.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["The mandibular division (V3) of the trigeminal nerve is responsible for motor innervation to the muscles of mastication.","The trigeminal nerve (CN V) has three divisions: ophthalmic (V1), maxillary (V2), and mandibular (V3).","V1 and V2 are purely sensory, while V3 has both sensory and motor functions."],"references":["Singh, V. (2023). Textbook of Anatomy-Head, Neck and Brain, Volume III-E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences","Patestas, M. A., \u0026 Gartner, L. P. (2016). A textbook of neuroanatomy. John Wiley \u0026 Sons","Patel, C. R., Fernandez-Miranda, J. C., Wang, W. H., \u0026 Wang, E. W. (2016). Skull Base Anatomy. Otolaryngologic clinics of North America, 49(1), 9\u201320. https://doi.org/10.1016/j.otc.2015.09.001","Anderson, B. W., Kortz, M. W., Black, A. C., \u0026 Al Kharazi, K. A. (2023). Anatomy, Head and Neck, Skull. In StatPearls. StatPearls Publishing"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data"